  "prompt": "Has anyone ever interviewed as a front end developer at Craigslist?",
  "response": "While there is no publicly available, centralized database specifically chronicling interviews for a Front-End Developer position at Craigslist, you can find information and experiences shared by individuals on websites like Glassdoor, Indeed, or LinkedIn. These platforms often feature reviews and feedback from candidates who have interviewed at various companies, including Craigslist. Additionally, tech-focused communities like Stack Overflow or forums on Reddit might have discussions or threads related to interviews at Craigslist.\n\nIf you are specifically looking for insights into the technical interviewing process or the types of questions asked, these websites would be helpful resources. On Glassdoor, for example, you can search for Craigslist and navigate to their interview section to read more about the experience and preparation tips shared by other users.",
